'You have come far, [placeholder], over hill and beneath the woods, but I speak not only of your weary travels...I speak, too, of your mind's strength. A true hunter strengthens his body and his mind, the better to face the perils of the wilderness.

'Few indeed possess the skill you have attained, [placeholder], and I direct you now to one such hunter, a Man by the name of Fenton Marshley. He makes his home at the Hunting Lodge once marshalled by Jon Brackenbook.

'Speak to Fenton outside the Hunting Lodge east of the town of Archet, for he will surely have words of interest to you.'
